Basic setup & information:

###docker version
Verify setup after install  (check Docker client +daemon version)

###docker info
check total running containers (show system info containers, images,etc.......)

###systemctl status docker
Troubleshoort "cannot connect to daemon" (check if docker daemon is active)

###systemctl start docker
Start daemon on Linux VM (Start Docker service)

==================================================================================

Image Managment commands:

###docker images
see which app versions are built (List all avialable images locally)

###docker pull <image>
docker pull amazonlinux (Download image from registory)

###docker rmi <image>
Remove an image

###docker image prune
Free up disk space on host (Clean up unused images)

======================================================================================

Container Lifecycle commands:

###docker ps 
shows all even stopped (show running containers)

###docker run <image>
Run a new container

###docker start <cid>
start stopped container

###docker stop <cid>
stop running container

###docker restart <cid>
common after config change (Restart container)

###docker rm <cid>
remove container

###docker exec -it <cid/name> bash
Debug live container (open shell inside container)

###docker logs -f <cid/name>
Monitor container output (View live logs)

###docker pause <cid/name>
Pause the container (can't login, start & stop)

###docker unpause <cid/name>
start the service if it's paused state

###docker commit "cid/name"
container to image converter.

